ENTRY            G3147   20251013   20260508   20260508       G059
SUBENT        G3147001   20251013   20260508   20260508       G059
BIB                 12         34
TITLE      An alternative method for determining the isomeric
            yield ratio and its application for 102m,gRh formed
            in 103Rh(g,n) reaction with 60, 65, and 70 MeV
            bremsstrahlung
AUTHOR     (Le Tuan Anh, Pham Duc Khue, Nguyen Van Do, Guinyn Kim,
            Phan Viet Cuong, Le Xuan Chung, Do Thi Khanh Linh,
            Bui Thi Hoa, Nguyen Dinh Khai, Nguyen Hoang Anh)
INSTITUTE  (3VN STH,3VN IPH,3KORKNU,3KORPUE)
           (3VN VN) Hanoi Irradiation Center, VINATOM
           (3VN VN) Hanoi University of Science, VNU
           (3VN VN) Military Institute of Radiation & Oncology
                    Medicine
           (3VN VN) Inspectorate Division,Vietnam Agency for
                    Radiation Safety
REFERENCE  (J,NIM/A,1080,170746,2025)
FACILITY   (LINAC,3KORPUE) Pohang Accelerator Laboratory (PAL)
INC-SOURCE (BRST) Pulsed electron beam on 0.1 mm thick tungsten
            target
SAMPLE     103Rh foil (purity: 99.9%, size: 12 mm x 12 mm,
            thickness: 0.10 mm)
METHOD     (ACTIV,GSPEC) Irradiated for repetition rate of 15 Hz
            and a pulse width 1.2 micro-sec
            60 MeV: irradiation for 120 min, 45 mA
            65 MeV: irradiation for 10 min, 85 mA
            70 MeV: irradiation for 60 min, 50 mA
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Energy resolution of 1.8 keV FWHM at 1332.5 keV
            peak of 60Co relative to a 3 inch diameter x 3 inch
            length NaI(Tl) detector
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) counting statistics combined with
            systematic uncertainties attributable to the
            experimental method. Other uncertainties were obtained
            via the uncertainty propagation method.
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by Le Tuan Anh (2025-10-13)
HISTORY    (20251013C) L.T.Anh and S.C.Yang
ENDBIB              34
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           37
